<body>
	<h1>Earthquakes: Understanding the Basics</h1>
	<p>An earthquake is a sudden release of energy in the Earth's lithosphere, creating seismic waves.</p>
	
	<h2>Causes of Earthquakes</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Tectonic plate movement</li>
		<li>Volcanic activity</li>
		<li>Human activities (e.g., injection of fluids into the ground)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>Effects of Earthquakes</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Ground shaking</li>
		<li>Soil liquefaction</li>
		<li>Tsunamis</li>
		<li>Structural damage to buildings</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>Preparedness and Safety</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Create an emergency plan</li>
		<li>Secure heavy objects</li>
		<li>Practice earthquake drills</li>
	</ul>
</body>
